qas.question: When did Protestant James Cameron bring the Gospel to the Tibetan people?
When did a large number of Lisu people convert to Christianity?
How were James O. Fraser, Alfred James Broomhall, and Isobel Kuhn involved with Tibet?

plausible_answers.text: Chongqing to Batang in Garzê Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture, Sichuan province

qas.question: Where did Cameron James walk in 1877?
Who was James O. Broomhall and Alfred James Fraser?

context: In <a0_0>1877<a0_0/>, the <b5_0>Protestant James Cameron<b5_0/> from <b4_0>the China Inland Mission<b4_0/> walked from <b3_0>Chongqing to Batang in Garzê Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture, Sichuan province<b3_0/>, and "brought the Gospel to the Tibetan people." <a1_0>Beginning in the 20th century<a1_0/>, in Diqing Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture in Yunnan, a large number of Lisu people and some Yi and Nu people converted to Christianity. <a2_0><b6_0>Famous earlier missionaries<b6_0/><a2_0/> include James O.
